# Security & auth

## Authentication (required on ALL endpoints)
- Every route is authenticated by default. Use a global guard; opt OUT explicitly per-route
  (e.g. health check) rather than opting in. No endpoint is anonymous by accident.
- For a local-runnable PoC, JWT (bearer) is the pragmatic choice: a global `JwtAuthGuard`,
  a `@Public()` decorator to exempt health/metrics. Document the chosen scheme in DECISIONS.md.
- Validate tokens fully: signature, expiry, issuer, audience. Reject on any failure with 401.

## Secrets & config
- No secrets in the repo. JWT secret / DB creds / Kafka creds come from env, validated at boot.
- Provide `.env.example` with placeholder values; real `.env` is gitignored.

## Input & output hygiene
- Global `ValidationPipe({ whitelist: true, forbidNonWhitelisted: true, transform: true })`.
- Parameterized queries only — no string-concatenated SQL (the atomic capacity update uses bound params).
- Rate-limit mutating endpoints if time permits (`@nestjs/throttler`).
- Never log secrets, tokens, or full account identifiers. Mask sensitive fields.

## Money-endpoint specifics
- Enforce `Idempotency-Key` on mutations; reject replays that carry a different body under the same key.
- Return precise, non-ambiguous amounts (minor units + currency), never locale-formatted floats.
- Authorization: a caller should only affect programs they're entitled to. If scoping exists,
  enforce it in the service, not just the controller.
